==English==
===Etymology 1===
Old English [[wund]] ''noun'', [[wundian]] ''verb''.

===Noun===
'''wound'''  (''plural'' '''[[wounds]]''')

#An [[injury]], such as a [[cut]] or [[tear]], to a (usually external) part of the body.
#:''The victim had a fatal '''wound''' to the back.'' 
#A [[hurt]] to a person's [[feeling]]s.
#:''It took a long time to get over the '''wound''' of that insult.''

====Pronunciation====
*wo͞ond, /wuːnd/, /<tt>wu:nd</tt>/

====Synonyms====
*(''injury''): [[injury]], [[lesion]]
*(''something that offends a person's feelings''): [[slight]], [[slur]], [[insult]]

